{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nPackage the auto-lander loop service and wire it into the existing compose stack on the Gerrit box, single-instance. Split out of S5 (`perpetual-ultrasonic-raccoon`) to keep each unit loadable whole.\n\n## Files\n- `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` — NEW: service image (installs the stdlib loop; `HEALTHCHECK` added by S5d).\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml` — EDIT: add the `autolander` service (labeled `autoheal=true`, per S5d) + the `willfarrell/autoheal` sidecar (Docker socket mounted **read-write** — autoheal issues `docker restart`, a daemon WRITE, so `:ro` would silently fail; the socket-write privilege is the accepted, inherent cost of autoheal) + declare the named state volume `gerrit_autolander` as `external: true`.\n- `infra/scripts/compose-up.sh` — EDIT: add `autolander` to `SITE_SUBDIRS` (the `volume_for_subdir()` helper prefixes `gerrit_` + maps `-`→`_`, so the subdir `autolander` yields the docker volume `gerrit_autolander` — the exact name used in `docker-compose.yml`). Incident-2731 drift gate: `config-check.sh` check 5 hard-fails CI when an `external: true` volume is missing from `SITE_SUBDIRS`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `infra/compose/Dockerfile.autolander` (new) + the `autolander` compose service added to the existing `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`.\n- [ ] **Single-instance guard:** the container acquires a POSIX advisory **file lock** (`flock` on the concrete lockfile **`autolander.lock`** at the root of its mounted state volume) on start; a second copy fails to acquire it and exits non-zero. This `flock` is the **sole** single-instance mechanism — do NOT rely on `deploy.replicas: 1` (a Swarm-only key silently ignored by plain `docker compose`).\n- [ ] **State volume:** the named volume **`gerrit_autolander`** is declared `external: true` and its subdir `autolander` added to `SITE_SUBDIRS` in `compose-up.sh`; it holds `autolander.lock`, the heartbeat file (S5d), the emergency-stop sentinel (S5d), and `recovery.json` (S5d), so all survive container recreation.\n- [ ] **Autoheal sidecar wired:** the `willfarrell/autoheal` service is present in `docker-compose.yml` with the Docker socket mounted **read-write** (required for its `docker restart` action), and the `autolander` service carries the `autoheal=true` label so the sidecar manages it (the restart behaviour itself is exercised by S5d's hang test).\n- [ ] **Tests:** `docker compose config` validates (autolander + autoheal services, `gerrit_autolander` external volume, `autoheal=true` label, read-write socket mount present); **flock proof (concrete):** `docker compose up -d autolander` then a second `docker run` on the same image + volume asserts exit code ≠ 0 within 10 s (the second instance fails the `flock`); `config-check.sh` check 5 passes (`autolander` in `SITE_SUBDIRS`)."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783838780030750001,"uuid":"4a7f312b-4cfa-4bba-b144-68203af97bb0"}